   Shailendran Sukhraj, thefather of slain nine-year-old, Sadia Sukhraj's took the stand in the Durban High Court on Tuesday where made an emotional statement during sentencing proceedings. Video Mphathi Nxumalo
  
 
 

 

 Defence advocate Sizwe Masondo had no questions for Shailendran.

 

 Nine-year-old Sadia died in a botched hijacking last year. The incident elicited public outrage.

 

 Mkhize was convicted on Monday for the murder of Sadia Sukhra. He was unemotional when he was convicted for murder and robbery. Sadia's death was one of the most high profile cases last year and it galvanised the Chatsworth community to protest against crime.

 

 
  







